### 📖 Explanation of Commands

| Command/Function | What it does |
| --- | --- |
| `nano [file]` | Opens a text editor in the terminal so you can write files without a mouse. |
| `pd.read_csv()` | Reads your text files and turns them into a "DataFrame" (a table Python understands). |
| `.fillna(0)` | Replaces "NaN" (empty spots) with 0 so the math doesn't break. |
| `.join()` | Combines two different tables into one. |
| `StandardScaler()` | Shrinks numbers so they are easier for the AI to compare (e.g., scale 1-100 to 0-1). |
| `.loc[...] = ...` | Finds specific rows that meet a condition (like an error) and fixes them. |
| `LogisticRegression()` | A standard machine learning model used to predict "Yes" (1) or "No" (0) for heart disease. |
| `.fit(X, y)` | The "Learning" phase where the model looks at features (X) to predict the target (y). |

